Comments from 18 parties addressed this issue specifically, with over half against the proposal. However, all those
comments opposing this proposal were conditional, suggesting that the restriction would be acceptable if it is limited
to the occupation in which the H-1B nonimmigrant is employed (

i.e.,

 nonimmigrant's employment would be permitted in an occupation other than one(s) subject to strike/lockout). Since
the proposal was, in fact, so limited, these commenters' concerns would be alleviated by careful attention to the
